In celebration of May the 4th, Walt Disney World has announced something huge is coming into the galaxy later this year. Guests staying at Walt Disney World Resort hotels and select other hotels will have the opportunity to enjoy Extra Magic Hours and Extra, Extra Magic Hours for a limited time. In celebration of the 25th anniversary of The Lion King, Jiko at Disney’s Animal Kingdom Lodge is going to offer a limited time dining experience. It will take place this summer and bring about some of your favorite moments from the Disney animated classic. Beginning on June 30, 2019, guests can head to Jiko – The […]

Disney’s Animal Kingdom has so many beautiful sights to see and so many wonderful animal friends to visit, but it’s always fantastic to welcome new ones. Disney has announced the birth of a healthy baby western lowland gorilla to the family and they want all guests to welcome Grace. Kashata is the mother of Grace […]

A brand new Signature Celebration Package is coming to Walt Disney World and it’s going to bring even more enchantment to Magic Kingdom. The new event will combine the fun of a fireworks dessert party package along with the royalty of dinner at Cinderella’s Royal Table. The new Signature Celebration Package will have guests attend […]

Huge news was announced yesterday for Disney’s Hollywood Studios as there was new concept art for Mickey & Minnie’s Runaway Railway as well as the new table-service restaurant coming to Toy Story Land. On Wednesday, the 30th anniversary of the park, Disney unveiled a brand new logo for Studios which will soon be up everywhere. […]

We recently reported that Mickey & Minnie’s Runaway Railway would also be built at Disneyland Park for an opening in 2022. We also found out that the opening date for the version at Disney’s Hollywood Studios was being pushed to “spring 2020,” but today, we have new details and concept art for this awesome new […]

As the 30th anniversary of Disney’s Hollywood Studios is just about upon us, some huge news has already been announced as Toy Story Land is going to be getting a table-service dining location/restaurant. Currently, there is only the quick-service location with Woody’s Lunch Box, but this new restaurant in Toy Story Land will be a […]

There is magic all around the Walt Disney World Resort and so much beauty as well. If you’re heading there soon, make sure to head out Disney’s Fort Wilderness Resort & Campground to catch a look at Lilly, the newest “Cinderella Pony” to arrive. Lilly is the first-ever white Shetland pony born at the Tri-Circle-D […]

It has been two years since the last time it took place, but the Blue Angels of the United States Navy are heading back to Walt Disney World next week. On the morning of May 2, 2019, Walt Disney World will honor the women and men of the military during Military Appreciation Month. Right around […]

Believe it or not, we are less than four months from the first Mickey’s Not-So-Scary Halloween Party of 2019, and that will bring a brand new fireworks show.
